  "texts": [
    "Despite the high median performances of the best performing model GPT-4, the full score of 5/5 points was reached only in 18, 24, and 26 out of 110 cases for the tasks diagnosis, examination and treatment respectively.",
    "All tools performed worse in rare diseases compared to frequent ones, which was anticipated as rare diseases are under-represented in large text corpora on the internet.",
    "From a technical perspective, the results are promising as GPT-3•5 and GPT-4 were never trained particularly for such clinical decision support tasks and perform in a considerable amount of cases significantly better than naïve Google search while saving search time and utilizing a more intuitive chatbot functionality to users.",
    "From a clinical point of view, we have to conclude that there are few but still a noticeable number of cases, in which all of the two models could not reach the highest score.",
    "This could lead to misunderstandings or medical issues if patients rely on these outputs without contacting trained health professionals."
  ],
